Package org.pathvisio.core.view

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnchorShape
    AnchorShape is responsible for defining the graphic for Anchors, similar to ArrowShape for Arrows.
    ArrowShape
    ArrowShapes determine how the ending of a line can be drawn.
    GenMAPPShapes
    This defines and registers some Special Shapes that are very specific to GenMAPP, such as the GenMAPP ProteinComplex, Vesicle and Ribosome.
    LinAlg
    Helper class for rotation calculations.
    LinAlg.Point
    Point, pair of doubles.
    MIMShapes
    Collection of Shapes and ArrowHeads used in the Molecular Interaction Map - style of pathways
    ShapeRegistry
    The Shape registry stores all arrow heads and shapes at this moment the shape registry initializes itself, by calling registerShape() on BasicShapes, GenMAPPShapes and MIMShapes.
    State
    represents the view of a PathwayElement with ObjectType.STATE.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ArrowShape.FillType
    Enumerates possible ways to combine the outline and body.
    GenMAPPShapes.Internal
    these constants are internal, only for the switch statement below.
